This document ensures the bearer has registered with the Brost County Mayor's office.  Much like the Tethyr-spanning Writ of Travel this document is used to identify travelers within the County, acknowledge that they understand the local laws, and provide them with the appropriate legal protections under said laws.

Additionally, since Brost is the magisterial center of the Duchy of Noromath, this document also signifies to officials of the other Baronies that the bearer is indeed a legally recognized traveler.
